defaultCase E - defaultForeign national mother in prisondefault&#xa0;
defaultBB was a foreign national who gave birth to a baby with disabilities while on remand.  She spoke no English. After her sentence she was informed that the baby would be removed as they did not know if she would be allowed to remain with her baby when she 
defaultwa
defaults eventually returned to 
defaultSpain
default.  After taking legal advice it was possible to establish that the Spanish authorities would accept her home to serve her sentence and would allow her to remain with her baby.  The decision was reversed.  Aside from the human 
defaultcosts of an unnecessary separation of mother and child, the cost to the public purse would have been enormous.
default BB would have fallen foul of the residence test because, although an EU citizen, she was not present in the 
defaultUK
default 
defaultas a result of 
defaultexercising EU right
defaults and had no other 
defaultright of residence.
